<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-09-05"><hi rend="italic">September 5,
                                    1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1333.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 2566, of July 22, 1896, and to express the Department’s
                            gratification at the settlement of the claim of the American Baptist
                            Missionary Union for losses in Szechuan, amounting to 14,305 taels,
                            which have been paid by the Government of China through the Shanghai
                            taotai.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>